  "name": "Ghast Stiletto",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>A <em>ghast stiletto</em> is a <em>+1 dagger</em> wrapped in the still-undead skin of a ghast. While you wield the dagger, you gain a +1 status bonus to all saves against paralysis.</p>\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">1</span> command, Interact (divine, necromancy, olfactory)</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per hour</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The ghast stiletto afflicts the next living target struck by the dagger with a terrible wound that emits the foul stench of the grave. For the next minute, the target creature, as well as any creatures within a @Template[type:emanation|distance:10], must succeed at a @Check[type:fortitude|dc:16|traits:divine,necromancy,olfactory] save or become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.fesd1n5eVhpCSS18]{Sickened 1} (plus @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.xYTAsEpcJE1Ccni3]{Slowed 1} as long as it's sickened on a critical failure). While within the emanation, the creature takes a â€“2 circumstance penalty to saves against disease and to recover from the sickened condition. A creature that succeeds at its save is temporarily immune for 1 minute.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Craft Requirements</strong> The initial raw materials must include skin from a ghast.</p>"
    },
